                <h1>How Far Back Do HireRight Criminal Background Checks Go?</h1>
                <p>HireRight criminal background checks typically go back seven years, consistent with the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA) guidelines. However, in some states, checks can cover longer periods, and certain convictions may be reported indefinitely. Employers should understand their state laws for compliance.</p>
